video.title: Outlander
video.synopsis: This epic tale adapted from Diana Gabaldon's popular series of fantasy-romance novels focuses on the drama of two time-crossed lovers.

episodes.synopsis: While on a second honeymoon in Scotland, former army nurse Claire stumbles on a gateway to the past and falls in with a band of Highland rebels.
episodes.title: Sassenach

episodes.synopsis: Claire arrives at the MacKenzie clan's castle and finds herself under suspicion from all sides. Jamie reveals a dark chapter from his past.
episodes.title: Castle Leoch

episodes.synopsis: Claire tries to embrace her role as healer but bristles at the harsh customs of the time -- and makes a powerful enemy of a local priest.
episodes.title: The Way Out

episodes.synopsis: As the clan prepares for an important gathering, Claire plots an escape from the castle. New tensions surface between Jamie and Dougal.
episodes.title: The Gathering

episodes.synopsis: On the road with Dougal and his men to collect rents, Claire encounters troubling scenes and begins to suspect a hidden scheme.
episodes.title: Rent

episodes.synopsis: Claire enjoys a warm welcome at a British outpost. But the arrival of a familiar face sours the mood and puts her in an uncomfortable position.
episodes.title: The Garrison Commander

episodes.synopsis: Claire wrestles with feelings of guilt as she and Jamie take a big step to keep Captain Randall at bay.
episodes.title: The Wedding

episodes.synopsis: Frank grows desperate in his search for Claire. Meanwhile, Claire and Jamie set out in search of a witness who may be able to clear Jamie's name.
episodes.title: Both Sides Now

episodes.synopsis: Sparks fly as Jamie confronts Claire about her trip to the stones. More trouble awaits the pair back at Castle Leoch.
episodes.title: The Reckoning

episodes.synopsis: The arrival of a duke raises Jamie's hopes and Claire's suspicions. Meanwhile, Claire confronts a rival and sees a troubling new side of Geillis.
episodes.title: By the Pricking of My Thumbs

episodes.synopsis: Claire discovers that Geillis may have another startling secret as they go on trial before an angry crowd. Later, Claire faces an agonizing decision.
episodes.title: The Devil's Mark

episodes.synopsis: Jamie takes Claire to his ancestral home, but long-simmering family tensions cast a cloud over their arrival.
episodes.title: Lallybroch

episodes.synopsis: The family scrambles to conceal Jamie's true identity from the members of the Watch. When Jenny goes into labor, Claire tries to ward off a crisis.
episodes.title: The Watch

episodes.synopsis: On a quest to find Jamie, Claire begins traveling the countryside as a performer and strikes a deal with Dougal.
episodes.title: The Search

episodes.synopsis: Claire and the others race to find a way into the prison, only to discover that Randall is there seeking his own twisted form of vengeance.
episodes.title: Wentworth Prison

episodes.synopsis: The men try one last ploy to free Jamie. But his encounter with Randall takes a heavy toll and leaves Claire grasping for answers.
episodes.title: To Ransom a Man's Soul

episodes.synopsis: Claire's worlds collide when she wakes up at the stones in 1948. Back in 1745, Claire and Jamie arrive in France and quickly earn a new enemy.
episodes.title: Through a Glass, Darkly

episodes.synopsis: In Paris, Jamie wrestles with his demons and obtains an unexpected audience with Prince Charles. Claire makes a troubling discovery at Versailles.
episodes.title: Not in Scotland Anymore

episodes.synopsis: As Jamie wades deeper into backroom politics, he discovers Prince Charles is keeping secrets from him. Claire finds a new use for her skills.
episodes.title: Useful Occupations and Deception

episodes.synopsis: Claire finally tells Jamie what she's been hiding, with surprising results. An evening designed to embarrass Prince Charles takes a chaotic turn.
episodes.title: La Dame Blanche

episodes.synopsis: Charles puts Jamie in an uncomfortable position, Claire intervenes in a delicate relationship, and a chilling encounter brings the past roaring back.
episodes.title: Untimely Resurrection

episodes.synopsis: Claire and Jamie move forward with the smallpox scheme and decide to let someone else in on their secret. A broken promise brings dire consequences.
episodes.title: Best Laid Schemes

episodes.synopsis: After an agonizing ordeal at the hospital, Claire sets out to win Jamie's freedom and finds herself in a delicate dance with the king.
episodes.title: Faith

episodes.synopsis: Back in Scotland, Claire and Jamie take a new approach to the rebellion. But their plan stirs up tensions with Jamie's grandfather and Clan MacKenzie.
episodes.title: The Fox's Lair

episodes.synopsis: As Jamie trains his motley band of men to fight, Claire is haunted by memories of World War II. A power struggle with Dougal threatens the mission.
episodes.title: Je Suis Prest

episodes.synopsis: Squabbles among the prince's advisers bog down the rebellion -- until a tip from a local reveals a way to catch the British off guard.
episodes.title: Prestonpans

episodes.synopsis: A sudden change of plans sends Claire and the Highlanders north, toward fresh trouble and an unexpected reunion.
episodes.title: Vengeance Is Mine

episodes.synopsis: While Jamie races to steer the Jacobites away from Culloden, Claire tends to an ailing Alex Randall and faces a weighty request from Colum MacKenzie.
episodes.title: The Hail Mary

episodes.synopsis: Long-buried secrets begin to emerge as Claire and her daughter visit Scotland in 1968. Back in 1746, Jamie takes drastic steps to save his loved ones.
episodes.title: Dragonfly in Amber

episodes.synopsis: Waking to a grim scene at Culloden, Jamie slowly pieces together his memories of the battle. Claire settles uneasily into her new life in Boston.
episodes.title: The Battle Joined

episodes.synopsis: Six years later, a broken Jamie hides out in the woods as the redcoats hound his family. Claire tries to make good on her promise of a fresh start.
episodes.title: Surrender

episodes.synopsis: As Brianna grows older, fresh cracks appear in Claire and Frank's marriage. Meanwhile, Jamie forges a tentative alliance with a new prison warden.
episodes.title: All Debts Paid

episodes.synopsis: Jamie navigates a dizzying string of complications at the Helwater estate. In 1968, Claire and Brianna search for clues to his life after Culloden.
episodes.title: Of Lost Things

episodes.synopsis: As Brianna struggles to readjust to life back at Harvard, a surprise visitor arrives for Christmas -- with news that leaves Claire reeling.
episodes.title: Freedom & Whiskey

episodes.synopsis: Passions and nerves run high as Claire steps into a printer's shop in Edinburgh for a moment decades in the making.
episodes.title: A. Malcolm

episodes.synopsis: A crisis forces Claire to put her medical training to use and sends Jamie scrambling to cover his tracks. Fergus helps Ian make a romantic connection.
episodes.title: Crme de Menthe

episodes.synopsis: Claire returns to Lallybroch, only to discover she's not as welcome as she once was. Jamie pays the price for keeping a secret too long.
episodes.title: First Wife

episodes.synopsis: As Jamie and Claire set sail on a rescue mission, life at sea proves full of turmoil, superstition and surprises.
episodes.title: The Doldrums

episodes.synopsis: While racing to stop the outbreak aboard the Porpoise, Claire makes a troubling discovery. A request from Jamie puts Fergus in a bind.
episodes.title: Heaven and Earth

episodes.synopsis: Washing ashore on an unfamiliar island, Claire battles the elements as she searches desperately for signs of civilization -- and a way back to Jamie.
episodes.title: Uncharted

episodes.synopsis: In Jamaica, Ian finds himself at the mercy of a mysterious figure. The Frasers attend a lavish ball at the governor's home, where surprises abound.
episodes.title: The Bakra

episodes.synopsis: At Rose Hall, Claire slowly realizes what Ian's captor is really after. A showdown takes shape at a cave rumored to have supernatural properties.
episodes.title: Eye of the Storm

episodes.synopsis: Four months after arriving in America, Jamie and Claire bid farewell to a friend, cross paths with a pirate and weigh an offer from a governor.
episodes.title: America the Beautiful

episodes.synopsis: Jamie's Aunt Jocasta welcomes the weary travelers to her lavish plantation, where Claire's views on slavery soon stir up trouble.
episodes.title: Do No Harm

episodes.synopsis: Claire and Jamie head into the mountains, where bad weather makes for a dramatic night. Sparks fly when Roger and Brianna meet up for a festival.
episodes.title: The False Bride

episodes.synopsis: As the Frasers start work on their new home, unsettling encounters put them on edge. Roger calls Brianna to share a big discovery.
episodes.title: Common Ground

episodes.synopsis: While helping deliver a baby, Claire becomes caught in a bitter dispute. Jamie gets a big surprise when he travels to town to recruit new tenants.
episodes.title: Savages

episodes.synopsis: A pair of unexpected visitors bring Jamie's memories of Helwater rushing back -- and stoke tensions at Fraser's Ridge.
episodes.title: Blood of My Blood

episodes.synopsis: After an unlucky start to her journey, Brianna finds refuge with someone who knew her father well. Meanwhile, Roger embarks on an odyssey of his own.
episodes.title: Down the Rabbit Hole

episodes.synopsis: As Roger searches the streets of Wilmington for Brianna, Jamie and Claire attend a play with Governor Tryon and learn of a troubling plan.
episodes.title: Wilmington

episodes.synopsis: Shaken by her ordeal, Brianna prepares to leave town. But news of Claire's feat at the theater upends her plans -- and leads to an emotional reunion.
episodes.title: The Birds & The Bees

episodes.synopsis: Brianna grows closer to Jamie as she weighs a decision about her future, but a shocking revelation soon tests their bond. Roger faces a grueling trek.
episodes.title: The Deep Heart's Core

episodes.synopsis: At River Run, a dinner party for a visiting lord puts Brianna in an awkward position. Meanwhile, Murtagh and Fergus hunt for Bonnet.
episodes.title: If Not For Hope

episodes.synopsis: News of Bonnet's fate draws Brianna and John to Wilmington. Roger befriends a fellow captive. Fergus and Marsali hatch a risky plan to help Murtagh.
episodes.title: Providence

episodes.synopsis: Jamie, Claire and Ian reach the Mohawk village, but their bid to buy Roger's freedom goes awry. At River Run, Brianna prepares for the baby's arrival.
episodes.title: Man of Worth
